<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The following notice is often found in my website logs. If this is not a bug, could the notice be supressed or sufficient checks put in place so that it is not raised.</p>

<p>[24-Aug-2006 11:03:51] PHP Notice:  iconv() [<a href="function.iconv">function.iconv</a>]: Detected an illegal character in input string in ZendFramework-0.1.5/library/Zend/Search/Lucene/Field.php on line 61</p>

    </div>
</div>

